ation: \u201cthey will make their swords into plow blades\""}, {"ref": "and their spears into pruning-hooks", "text": "\"they will hammer their spears into pruning hooks.\" A pruning-hook is a knife that people use to cut off branches from a plant. Alternate translation: \u201cthey will make their spears into pruning knives.\""}, {"ref": "lift up sword", "text": "Alternate translation: \"fight.\""}]}, {"id": "02-05", "tn": [{"ref": "", "text": "In 2:5 Isaiah was speaking to the people of Israel."}, {"ref": "", "text": "In 2:6 Isaiah was speaking to God."}, {"ref": "O house of Jacob", "text": "\"you descendants of Jacob\" (UDB) or \"You people of Israel\" (See: [[en:ta:translate:metonymy]])"}, {"ref": "For you have abandoned your people", "text": "\"For you have rejected your people\" or \"For you have left your people.\" Here the word \"you\" refers to Yahweh."}, {"ref": "they are filled with customs from the east", "text": "\"they act like the people who live in lands east of Israel and do not know God\""}, {"ref": "omen readers", "text": "\"sooth sayers\" or \"diviners.\" This refers to people who claim to know what will happen the future."}, {"ref": "and they shake hands with sons of foreigners", "text": "Alternate translation: \"they make agreements with people who are not from Israel.\" (See: [[en:ta:translate:idiom]])"}, {"ref": "they worship the craftsmanship of their own hands, things that their own fingers have made.", "text": "Both of these phrases mean basically the same thing. Alternate translation: \"they worship things that they themselves have made.\" (See: [[en:ta:translate:doublet]])"}]}, {"id": "02-09", "tn": [{"ref": "", "text": "In 2:9 Isaiah was speaking to God. In 2:10-11 Isaiah was speaking to the people."}, {"ref": "The people will be bowed down, and individuals will fall down", "text": "The phrases \"the people\" and \"individuals\" used together means \"all people.\" Alternate translation: \"Every person will be made to bow down and be humb